    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Bono Romani imperii <lb n="2"/>procreato domino nostro <lb n="3"/><del rend="erasure">[<expan><abbr>Gal</abbr><ex>erio</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Val</abbr><ex>erio</ex></expan> Maximino</del>] <lb n="4"/>clementissimo et <lb n="5"/>victoriosissimo <expan><abbr>Caes</abbr><ex>ari</ex></expan> <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Lucil</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> Crispus <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ir</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>erfectissimus</ex></expan> praeses <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>prov</abbr><ex>inciae</ex></expan> Isauriae <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>evotus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>umini</ex></expan> m<expan><ex>aiestati</ex><abbr>q</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> <lb n="8"/>eius
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Datierung: Gleichzeitigkeit dieser Inschrift mit der in AE 1978, 814 publizierten (vom selben Dedikanten). Der Caesar ist vermutlich eher Maximinus Daia als Maxentius. Zwei aneinanderpassende Fragmente. (B): ETAM 22: Z. 6: Lucilius.</p>
            </div>
